---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout 
  title="Medical Disclaimer & Terms of Use | CompareWeightMeds"
  description="Important medical disclaimer, affiliate disclosure, and terms of use for CompareWeightMeds. This site provides informational content only and does not offer medical advice."
>
  <style>
    .hero {
      background: linear-gradient(135deg, #10b981 0%, #059669 100%);
      color: white;
      padding: 80px 24px 60px;
      text-align: center;
    }
    
    .hero h1 {
      font-size: clamp(2.2rem, 5vw, 3rem);
      font-weight: 700;
      margin-bottom: 16px;
    }
    
    .content {
      max-width: 900px;
      margin: 0 auto;
      padding: 60px 24px 80px;
    }
    
    .content h2 {
      font-size: 2rem;
      font-weight: 700;
      margin: 48px 0 16px;
      color: var(--accent);
    }
    
    .content h3 {
      font-size: 1.5rem;
      font-weight: 600;
      margin: 32px 0 12px;
    }
    
    .content p {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text-sec);
      margin-bottom: 20px;
    }
    
    .content ul {
      margin: 20px 0;
      padding-left: 24px;
    }
    
    .content li {
      font-size: 1.05rem;
      line-height: 1.7;
      color: var(--text-sec);
      margin-bottom: 12px;
    }
    
    .warning-box {
      background: #fef3c7;
      border-left: 4px solid #f59e0b;
      padding: 24px;
      border-radius: var(--r);
      margin: 32px 0;
    }
    
    .warning-box h3 {
      color: #92400e;
      margin: 0 0 12px 0;
    }
    
    .warning-box p {
      color: #92400e;
      margin: 0;
    }
  </style>

  <div class="hero">
    <h1>Medical Disclaimer & Terms of Use</h1>
  </div>

  <div class="content">
    <div class="warning-box">
      <h3>⚠️ Important Medical Disclaimer</h3>
      <p>CompareWeightMeds is an informational resource and comparison platform. We are not a medical provider, pharmacy, or healthcare institution. We do not prescribe medications, provide medical advice, diagnose conditions, or offer treatment recommendations.</p>
    </div>
    
    <h2>Medical Disclaimer</h2>
    
    <h3>Not Medical Advice</h3>
    <p>All content on CompareWeightMeds.com (the "Site"), including but not limited to text, reviews, comparisons, scores, graphics, images, and other materials, is provided for informational and educational purposes only. This content is not intended to be, and should not be interpreted as, medical advice, diagnosis, or treatment.</p>
    
    <h3>Consult Your Healthcare Provider</h3>
    <p>Always seek the advice of your physician or other qualified healthcare provider with any questions you may have regarding a medical condition, weight loss medication, or treatment plan. Never disregard professional medical advice or delay seeking it because of something you read on this Site.</p>
    
    <h3>Emergency Medical Situations</h3>
    <p>If you think you may have a medical emergency, call your doctor, go to the emergency department, or call emergency services immediately. CompareWeightMeds does not recommend or endorse any specific tests, physicians, products, procedures, opinions, or other information that may be mentioned on the Site.</p>
    
    <h3>Individual Results May Vary</h3>
    <p>Weight loss results from GLP-1 medications (semaglutide, tirzepatide, liraglutide, etc.) vary significantly between individuals. Factors affecting results include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Starting weight and body composition</li>
      <li>Diet and exercise habits</li>
      <li>Genetic factors and metabolism</li>
      <li>Underlying medical conditions</li>
      <li>Medication dosage and adherence</li>
      <li>Duration of treatment</li>
    </ul>
    <p>The experiences of other patients do not guarantee your results will be similar.</p>
    
    <h2>Prescription Medication Information</h2>
    
    <h3>Prescription Required</h3>
    <p>GLP-1 medications including semaglutide (Ozempic, Wegovy), tirzepatide (Mounjaro, Zepbound), and liraglutide (Saxenda, Victoza) are prescription medications that require evaluation and approval by a licensed healthcare provider. These medications are not appropriate for everyone and may have contraindications based on your medical history.</p>
    
    <h3>Side Effects and Risks</h3>
    <p>GLP-1 medications can cause side effects, some serious. Common side effects include nausea, vomiting, diarrhea, constipation, and abdominal pain. Serious risks may include:</p>
    <ul>
      <li>Pancreatitis (inflammation of the pancreas)</li>
      <li>Gallbladder problems</li>
      <li>Kidney problems</li>
      <li>Hypoglycemia (low blood sugar)</li>
      <li>Thyroid tumors (animal studies; risk in humans unknown)</li>
      <li>Allergic reactions</li>
      <li>Changes in vision (diabetic retinopathy complications)</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Discuss all risks and benefits with your healthcare provider before starting treatment.</p>
    
    <h3>Compounded Medications</h3>
    <p>Some telehealth providers offer compounded versions of semaglutide and tirzepatide. Important facts about compounded medications:</p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Not FDA-Approved:</strong> Compounded medications are not approved by the FDA for safety, efficacy, or quality</li>
      <li><strong>Legally Manufactured:</strong> When sourced from licensed 503A or 503B compounding pharmacies, compounded medications are legal and regulated by state boards of pharmacy</li>
      <li><strong>Cost vs Quality Trade-off:</strong> Compounded medications typically cost 50-70% less than brand-name versions but lack FDA oversight</li>
      <li><strong>Same Active Ingredients:</strong> Compounded versions use the same active pharmaceutical ingredients (semaglutide or tirzepatide) as brand-name medications</li>
    </ul>
    
